This topic describes how to manage <%= vars.product_full %> if you change the password for infrastructure such as vSphere and NSX-T.  

## <a id='vcenter-pw-change'></a> vCenter Password Change

If, after deploying <%= vars.product_short %> on vSphere, the vCenter password is changed, perform the following operations:

1. Update the [vCenter password in the BOSH tile](#bosh-pw-change-vc).
1. Update the [vCenter password in the PKS tile](#pks-pw-change-vc).
1. Deploy <%= vars.product_short %> and [update all Kubernetes clusters].

### <a id='bosh-pw-change-vc'></a> Step 1: Update the vCenter Password in the BOSH Director Tile

1. Access the **Installation Dashboard** in Ops Manager.
1. Edit the BOSH Director tile.
1. Select the **vCenter Config** tab.
1. Click the **Change** link beneath the **vCenter Password** field.
1. Enter the new password and click **Save**.
  <img src="images/vsphere/pw-change-bosh-vc.png" alt="vCenter Password Update in BOSH">
1. Click **Save** to save the changes to the BOSH Director tile.

### <a id='pks-pw-change-vc'></a> Step 2: Update the vCenter Password in the the PKS Tile

1. Access the **Installation Dashboard** in Ops Manager.
1. Edit the BOSH Director tile.
1. Select the **Kubernetes Cloud Provider** tab.
1. Click the **Change** link beneath the **vCenter Master Credentials** field.
1. Enter the new password and click **Save**.
  <img src="images/vsphere/pw-change-pks-vc.png" alt="vCenter Password Update in PKS">

### <a id='deploy-pks'></a> Step 3: Deploy Enterprise PKS

Because the vCenter password is stored in Kubernetes clusters (for the Kubernetes cloud provider), you must apply the tile changes with the cluster upgrade errand enabled. 

1. Access the **Installation Dashboard** in Ops Manager.
1. Click **Review Pending Changes**.
1. In the **Errands** section for <%= vars.product_short %>, verify that the "Update all clusters errand" is selected. If it is not selected, select it.
1. Click **Apply Changes** to update the installation of <%= vars.product_short %>.

## <a id='vcenter-pw-change'></a> NSX Manager Password Change

If, after deploying <%= vars.product_short %> on vSphere, the NSX Manager password is changed, perform the following operation:

1. Access the **Installation Dashboard** in Ops Manager.
1. Edit the BOSH Director tile.
1. Select the **vCenter Config** tab.
1. Click the **Change** link beneath the **NSX Username** field.
1. Enter the new password and click **Save**.
  <img src="images/vsphere/pw-change-bosh-nsx.png" alt="NSX Manager Password Update in BOSH">
1. Click **Save** to save the changes to the BOSH Director tile.
1. At the **Installation Dashboard**, click **Review Pending Changes**.
1. Click **Apply Changes**.


